com.salesforce.omakase.ast.declaration

Interface FunctionValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Broadcastable, Groupable<PropertyValue,PropertyValueMember>, Named, PropertyValueMember, Syntax, Term, Writable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenericFunctionValue, LinearGradientFunctionValue, UrlFunctionValue

    public interface FunctionValue
extends Term, Named
    General interface for function term values, such as GenericFunctionValue.

    In contrast to RawFunction, this interface is implemented by all specific functions. RawFunctions on the other hand represent functions that have yet to be refined into the specific function.

    In other words, subscribe to FunctionValue if you would like to receive all specific function value instances, and subscribe to RawFunction if you would like to refine a standard or custom function.

    See Also:
    GenericFunctionValue
